The vegetarian federation Germany suggests a set of veganen alternatives on the occasion of the Weltvegantags on 1 November:
Pure plant margarine is a good alternative to butter, yogurt lets by soy yogurt replace.
Instead of milk can be used soy, oats, almond or rice milk.
Impact-cash plant cream replaces conventional whipped cream.
Also to eggs there are vegetable alternatives.
A half crushed, ripe banana for example can replace an egg as bonding agents in a cake.
Also 50 gram of apple mash or a tablespoon ground flax seeds plus three tablespoons water are suitable for it.
Pastes become loose instead of with egg for example with a mixture from a teaspoonful baking powder, a tablespoon food strength and three tablespoons mineral waters.
In addition, 50 gram soy yogurt or Seidentofu can serve this purpose.
According to the Vebu at present approximately 800,000 humans nourish themselves vegan, thus purely vegetable in Germany.
